results.name: Number of divisors of n that are primitively abundant (A091191).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..70560
example: Divisors of 24 are 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 12, 24. Only 12 is in A091191, thus a(24) = 1.
Divisors of 36 are 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 9, 12, 18, 36. Of these 12 and 18 are found in A091191, thus a(36) = 2.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Nov 14 2017
